">pNilradical</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">p</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Nilpotent/Lemmas.html#nilradical\">nilradical</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsPerfectClosure.html#pNilradical_le_nilradical","kind":"theorem","line":77,"name":"pNilradical_le_nilradical","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsPerfectClosure.lean#L77-L81"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsPerfectClosure.html#pNilradical\"><span class=\"name\">pNilradical</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommSemiring\">CommSemiring</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given a natural number `p`, the `p`-nilradical of a ring is defined to be the\nnilradical if `p > 1` (`pNilradical_eq_nilradical`), and defined to be the zero ideal if `p ≤ 1`\n(`pNilradical_eq_bot'`). Equivalently, it is the ideal consisting of elements `x` such that\n`x ^ p ^ n = 0` for some `n` (`mem_pNilradical`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsPerfectClosure.html#pNilradical","kind":"def","line":71,"name":"pNilradical","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsPerfectClosure.lean#L71-L75"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.FieldTheory.PurelyInseparable.Basic","Mathlib.FieldTheory.PerfectClosure"],"instances":[{"className":"IsPRadical","name":"IsPRadical.of_id","typeNames":["RingHom.id"]},{"className":"IsPRadical","name":"PerfectClosure.isPRadical","typeNames":["PerfectClosure.of"]},{"className":"IsPRadical","name":"IsPurelyInseparable.isPRadical","typeNames":["algebraMap"]}],"name":"Mathlib.FieldTheory.IsPerfectClosure"}